        "content": "<p>I have the following proof:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">example</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">ℚ</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"bp\">*</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">/</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"bp\">∨</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"bp\">-</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">/</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">right</span>\n  <span class=\"k\">calc</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"bp\">*</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"bp\">-</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\">/</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span> <span class=\"n\">ring</span> <span class=\"c1\">-- /1</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">_</span> <span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span> <span class=\"bp\">-</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\">/</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span> <span class=\"n\">rel</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"c1\">-- /2</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">_</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"bp\">-</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">/</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span> <span class=\"n\">linarith</span> <span class=\"c1\">-- /3</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>In /1, I create something equal to <code>b</code> that allows me to use <code>rel [h]</code> in /2.  </p>\n<p>I interpret the <code>_</code> in /2 as referencing <code>b</code>, as in b is less than [the stuff after the less than].  Is that correct?</p>\n<p>Would someone please explain why I use an <code>=</code> in /3?  I assume the  <code>_</code> still refers to <code>b</code>,  so I don't understand the equality.</p>",
